TITLE: Creating Kibana Security Role with Base Privileges (Terraform)
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform code creates a Kibana security role with base privileges. It defines Elasticsearch cluster and index privileges, as well as Kibana base privileges and spaces. The Elasticsearch configuration includes cluster-level privileges and index-level privileges with field security. The Kibana configuration includes base privileges applied to the specified spaces.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/kibana_security_role.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {}
  kibana {}
}

resource "elasticstack_kibana_security_role" "example" {
  name = "sample_role"
  elasticsearch {
    cluster = ["create_snapshot"]
    indices {
      field_security {
        grant  = ["test"]
        except = []
      }
      names      = ["test"]
      privileges = ["create", "read", "write"]
    }
    remote_indices {
      field_security {
        grant  = ["test"]
        except = []
      }
      names      = ["test"]
      clusters   = ["test-cluster"]
      privileges = ["create", "read", "write"]
    }
  }
  kibana {
    base   = ["all"]
    spaces = ["default"]
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Create Elasticsearch Component Template (Mappings) - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates an Elasticsearch Component Template named `my_mappings`. It defines the mappings for index fields, specifying data types such as keyword, text, and date. It's used to ensure consistency across indices.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/guides/elasticstack-kibana-rule.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
// Create a component template for mappings
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_component_template" "my_mappings" {
  name = "my_mappings"
  template {
    mappings = jsonencode({
      properties = {
        field1       = { type = "keyword" }
        field2       = { type = "text" }
        "@timestamp" = { type = "date" }
      }
    })
  }
}
```

