TITLE: Creating Elasticsearch Security User with Plaintext Password
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration creates an Elasticsearch security user named "devuser" with a plaintext password.  It configures the user with the 'kibana_user' role and sets custom metadata. The `elasticsearch_connection` is implicitly inherited from the provider block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_security_user.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_security_user" "dev" {
  username = "devuser"

  password = "1234567890"
  roles    = ["kibana_user"]

  // set the custom metadata for this user
  metadata = jsonencode({
    "env"    = "testing"
    "open"   = false
    "number" = 49
  })
}
```

