TITLE: Create Kibana Action Connector (Index) - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates a Kibana Action Connector named `my_index_connector`. It configures the connector to write documents to the specified Elasticsearch index with an `executionTimeField`. The connector will be used by the alert to send notifications.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/guides/elasticstack-kibana-rule.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_kibana_action_connector" "index_example" {
  name              = "my_index_connector"
  connector_type_id = ".index"
  config = jsonencode({
    index              = elasticstack_elasticsearch_index.my_index.name
    executionTimeField = "alert_date"
  })
}
```

