TITLE: Creating Index Template with Aliases and Settings in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration creates an Elasticsearch index template named 'my_template'. It defines index patterns, priority, aliases (my_template_test and another_test), and index settings including setting the number_of_shards to 3. It requires the elasticstack provider to be configured with Elasticsearch connectivity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_index_template.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {}
}

resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_index_template" "my_template" {
  name = "my_template"

  priority       = 42
  index_patterns = ["logstash*", "filebeat*"]

  template {
    alias {
      name = "my_template_test"
    }
    alias {
      name = "another_test"
    }

    settings = jsonencode({
      number_of_shards = "3"
    })
  }
}
```

