TITLE: Creating Kibana Action Connector for PagerDuty
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a Kibana action connector for PagerDuty integration. It requires the `.pagerduty` connector type ID. The configuration includes the PagerDuty API URL, and secrets contain the routing key obtained from a PagerDuty service integration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/kibana_action_connector.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_kibana_action_connector" "pagerduty-connector" {
  name              = "pagerduty"
  connector_type_id = ".pagerduty"
  config = jsonencode({
    apiUrl = "https://events.pagerduty.com/v2/enqueue"
  })
  secrets = jsonencode({
    routingKey = pagerduty_service_integration.kibana.integration_key
  })
}
```

