TITLE: Creating API Key with Role Descriptors and Metadata
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates an Elasticsearch security API key with a specified name, role descriptors, expiration time, and custom metadata. The role descriptors are defined using a JSON-encoded string, specifying cluster and index privileges. The expiration is set to 1 day. The metadata is also provided as a JSON-encoded string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_security_api_key.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_security_api_key" "api_key" {
  # Set the name
  name = "My API key"

  # Set the role descriptors
  role_descriptors = jsonencode({
    role-a = {
      cluster = ["all"],
      indices = [
        {
          names      = ["index-a*"],
          privileges = ["read"]
        }
      ]
    }
  })

  # Set the expiration for the API key
  expiration = "1d"

  # Set the custom metadata for this user
  metadata = jsonencode({
    "env"    = "testing"
    "open"   = false
    "number" = 49
  })
}
```

