TITLE: Creating Elasticsearch Security Role with Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource defines an Elasticsearch security role named 'testrole'. It assigns cluster-level privileges, index-level privileges for 'index1' and 'index2', application privileges for 'myapp', and specifies users who can be impersonated. It also includes metadata for the role.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_security_role.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {}
}

resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_security_role" "role" {
  name        = "testrole"
  description = "Role for testing"
  cluster     = ["all"]

  indices {
    names      = ["index1", "index2"]
    privileges = ["all"]
  }

  applications {
    application = "myapp"
    privileges  = ["admin", "read"]
    resources   = ["*"]
  }

  run_as = ["other_user"]

  metadata = jsonencode({
    version = 1
  })
}

output "role" {
  value = elasticstack_elasticsearch_security_role.role
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Import Fleet Integration Policy Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to import an existing Fleet Integration Policy into Terraform using the `terraform import` command.  It specifies the resource name `elasticstack_fleet_integration_policy.my_policy` and the `<fleet_integration_policy_id>` which is the unique identifier of the policy within Elastic Stack.  This allows Terraform to manage an existing policy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/fleet_integration_policy.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
terraform import elasticstack_fleet_integration_policy.my_policy <fleet_integration_policy_id>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Import Elasticsearch ILM Policy using Terraform
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to import an existing Elasticsearch index lifecycle management (ILM) policy into Terraform using the `terraform import` command. The command requires the cluster UUID and ILM policy name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_index_lifecycle.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
terraform import elasticstack_elasticsearch_index_lifecycle.my_ilm <cluster_uuid>/<ilm_name>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Update Elasticsearch Cluster Settings with Elasticstack Terraform Provider
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource block configures cluster-wide settings in Elasticsearch. It defines both persistent and transient settings for indices lifecycle poll interval, recovery, breaker limits and security audit logging. It requires the `elasticstack` provider to be configured.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_cluster_settings.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {}
}

resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_cluster_settings" "my_cluster_settings" {
  persistent {
    setting {
      name  = "indices.lifecycle.poll_interval"
      value = "10m"
    }
    setting {
      name  = "indices.recovery.max_bytes_per_sec"
      value = "50mb"
    }
    setting {
      name  = "indices.breaker.total.limit"
      value = "65%"
    }
    setting {
      name       = "xpack.security.audit.logfile.events.include"
      value_list = ["ACCESS_DENIED", "ACCESS_GRANTED"]
    }
  }

  transient {
    setting {
      name  = "indices.breaker.total.limit"
      value = "60%"
    }
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating Elasticsearch Transform with Pivot Aggregation in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates an Elasticsearch transform that uses a pivot aggregation to summarize data from a source index to a destination index. It configures the source, destination, pivot aggregation, frequency, retention policy, sync settings, and other optional parameters like max page search size and enabled state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_transform.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_transform" "transform_with_pivot" {
  name        = "transform-pivot"
  description = "A meaningful description"

  source {
    indices = ["names_or_patterns_for_input_index"]
  }

  destination {
    index = "destination_index_for_transform"

    aliases {
      alias            = "test_alias_1"
      move_on_creation = true
    }

    aliases {
      alias            = "test_alias_2"
      move_on_creation = false
    }
  }

  pivot = jsonencode({
    "group_by" : {
      "customer_id" : {
        "terms" : {
          "field" : "customer_id",
          "missing_bucket" : true
        }
      }
    },
    "aggregations" : {
      "max_price" : {
        "max" : {
          "field" : "taxful_total_price"
        }
      }
    }
  })

  frequency = "5m"

  retention_policy {
    time {
      field   = "order_date"
      max_age = "30d"
    }
  }

  sync {
    time {
      field = "order_date"
      delay = "10s"
    }
  }

  max_page_search_size = 2000

  enabled          = false
  defer_validation = false
}
```

