TITLE: Creating Kibana SLO with Custom Metric Indicator (Terraform)
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource shows how to create a Kibana SLO with a custom metric indicator. It requires Elastic Stack version 8.10.0 or later. The resource defines the SLO name, description, custom metric indicator, time window, budgeting method, and objective. The custom metric indicator defines the index, good and total conditions (metrics and equation).
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/kibana_slo.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_kibana_slo" "custom_metric" {
  name        = "custom kql"
  description = "custom kql"

  metric_custom_indicator {
    index = "my-index"
    good {
      metrics {
        name        = "A"
        aggregation = "sum"
        field       = "processor.processed"
      }
      equation = "A"
    }

    total {
      metrics {
        name        = "A"
        aggregation = "sum"
        field       = "processor.accepted"
      }
      equation = "A"
    }
  }

  time_window {
    duration = "7d"
    type     = "rolling"
  }

  budgeting_method = "timeslices"

  objective {
    target           = 0.95
    timeslice_target = 0.95
    timeslice_window = "5m"
  }

}
```

