TITLE: Creating Kibana SLO with Custom KQL Indicator (Terraform)
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates a Kibana SLO using a custom KQL (Kibana Query Language) indicator. It defines the SLO name, description, custom KQL indicator, time window, budgeting method, objective, and settings. The custom KQL indicator includes the index, good condition, total condition, filter, and timestamp field.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/kibana_slo.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_kibana_slo" "custom_kql" {
  name        = "custom kql"
  description = "custom kql"

  kql_custom_indicator {
    index           = "my-index"
    good            = "latency < 300"
    total           = "*"
    filter          = "labels.groupId: group-0"
    timestamp_field = "custom_timestamp"
  }

  time_window {
    duration = "7d"
    type     = "rolling"
  }

  budgeting_method = "timeslices"

  objective {
    target           = 0.95
    timeslice_target = 0.95
    timeslice_window = "5m"
  }

  settings {
    sync_delay = "5m"
    frequency  = "5m"
  }

}
```

