TITLE: Creating Ingest Pipeline with JSON Processors in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform code creates an Elasticsearch ingest pipeline named 'my_ingest_pipeline'. It defines two processors: a 'set' processor to set the '_meta' field and a 'json' processor to parse the 'data' field into 'parsed_data'. The processors are defined using jsonencode and a HERE DOC construct.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_ingest_pipeline.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {}
}

resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_ingest_pipeline" "my_ingest_pipeline" {
  name        = "my_ingest_pipeline"
  description = "My first ingest pipeline managed by Terraform"

  // processors can be defined in different way
  processors = [
    // using the jsonencode function, which is the recommended way if you want to provide JSON object by yourself
    jsonencode({
      set = {
        description = "My set processor description"
        field       = "_meta"
        value       = "indexed"
      }
    }),
    // or use the HERE DOC construct to provide the processor definition
    <<EOF
    {"json": {
      "field": "data",
      "target_field": "parsed_data"
    }}
EOF
    ,
  ]
}
```

