TITLE: Create Elasticsearch Index - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates an Elasticsearch index named `my-index`. It defines the mappings for the index fields, specifying data types and formats.  This is where alerts will be written.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/guides/elasticstack-kibana-rule.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_index" "my_index" {
  name = "my-index"
  mappings = jsonencode({
    properties = {
      alert_date = { type = "date", format = "date_optional_time||epoch_millis" }
      rule_id    = { type = "text" }
      rule_name  = { type = "text" }
      message    = { type = "text" }
    }
  })
}
```

