TITLE: Create Elasticsearch Index Lifecycle Policy (ILM) - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform resource creates an Elasticsearch Index Lifecycle Policy named `my_lifecycle_policy`. It defines the hot and delete phases with specific configurations such as minimum age, priority, rollover settings, and deletion criteria. It ensures that data is managed according to defined policies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/guides/elasticstack-kibana-rule.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
// Create an ILM policy for our data stream
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_index_lifecycle" "my_lifecycle_policy" {
  name = "my_lifecycle_policy"

  hot {
    min_age = "1h"
    set_priority {
      priority = 10
    }
    rollover {
      max_age = "1d"
    }
    readonly {}
  }

  delete {
    min_age = "2d"
    delete {}
  }
}
```

