TITLE: Creating a Mustache Search Template - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a search template in Elasticsearch using the `elasticstack_elasticsearch_script` resource. The script_id, language (mustache), and source (a JSON encoded query template) are defined. Parameters for the search template can also be defined. This allows for parameterized queries to be stored and reused.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/resources/elasticsearch_script.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_script" "my_search_template" {
  script_id = "my_search_template"
  lang      = "mustache"
  source = jsonencode({
    query = {
      match = {
        message = "{{query_string}}"
      }
