TITLE: Logstash Pipeline Metadata with jsonencode (Terraform)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define the `pipeline_metadata` field in a Logstash pipeline resource using the Elasticstack Terraform provider.  The `pipeline_metadata` field must be encapsulated with `jsonencode()` to ensure proper data handling and to address issues caused by updates to Logstash Pipelines outside of Terraform. This resolves issues arising from discrepancies in state management.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_logstash_pipeline" "example" {
  name = "example"
  pipeline = <<-EOF
    input{}
    filter{}
    output{}
EOF
  pipeline_metadata = jsonencode({
    type = "logstash_pipeline"
    version = 1
  })
}
```

