TITLE: Create Elasticsearch Enrich Policy Terraform
DESCRIPTION: Creates an Elasticsearch enrich policy named `policy1` of type `match`. It uses the `my_index` index created earlier, matches on the `email` field, and enriches with the `first_name` and `last_name` fields. A query is also defined to filter documents used for enrichment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/data-sources/elasticsearch_enrich_policy.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_enrich_policy" "policy1" {
  name          = "policy1"
  policy_type   = "match"
  indices       = [elasticstack_elasticsearch_index.my_index.name]
  match_field   = "email"
  enrich_fields = ["first_name", "last_name"]
  query = jsonencode({
    bool = {
      must     = [{ term = { b = "A" } }]
      must_not = [{ term = { a = "B" } }]
    }
  })
}
```

