TITLE: Configuring Elasticsearch with Static Credentials
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates configuring the Elasticstack provider to connect to Elasticsearch using static credentials (username and password). It includes the required Terraform provider block and the Elasticsearch provider configuration block with the `username`, `password`, and `endpoints` attributes. Ensure that the `endpoints` list include the http(s) schema and port number.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/index.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
terraform {
  required_version = ">= 1.0.0"
  required_providers {
    elasticstack = {
      source  = "elastic/elasticstack"
      version = "~>0.9"
    }
  }
}

provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {
    username  = "elastic"
    password  = "changeme"
    endpoints = ["http://localhost:9200"]
  }
}
```

