TITLE: Gsub Ingest Processor Configuration in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This Terraform configuration defines a provider for Elasticstack, retrieves configuration for an Elasticsearch gsub processor, and uses it to create an ingest pipeline. The gsub processor replaces all occurrences of a specified pattern in a given field with a replacement string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/terraform-provider-elasticstack/blob/main/docs/data-sources/elasticsearch_ingest_processor_gsub.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: terraform
CODE:
```
provider "elasticstack" {
  elasticsearch {}
}

data "elasticstack_elasticsearch_ingest_processor_gsub" "gsub" {
  field       = "field1"
  pattern     = "\\."
  replacement = "-"
}

resource "elasticstack_elasticsearch_ingest_pipeline" "my_ingest_pipeline" {
  name = "gsub-ingest"

  processors = [
    data.elasticstack_elasticsearch_ingest_processor_gsub.gsub.json
  ]
}
```

